The ashy-throated warbler (Phylloscopus maculipennis) is a species of leaf warbler (family Phylloscopidae). It was formerly included in the "Old World warbler" assemblage.
It is found in the Himalayas, Yunnan, Northeast IndiaÂ and northern Indochina. Its natural habitats are temperate forests and subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests.
